        FAQ3QH1.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 24)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QH1.setText("<html><b>Are there additional baggage allowances if I’m travelling with an infant?");
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QH1, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 30, -1, 30));

        FAQ3QC1.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 16)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QC1.setText("<html><b>Checked baggage</b>\n<br><br> Infant baggage allows one extra piece of baggage in addition to your usual baggage allowance, regardless of cabin class. This extra piece must be 23kgkilograms\n (50lbpounds) or less, with total dimensions (length +plus width +plus height) not exceeding 150cmcentimeters (59 inches). <br><br>\n <b>Cabin baggage</b><br><br> Passengers travelling with infants in any class are also permitted one (1) handbag for inflight necessities and infant food (weight must not exceed 5 kg/11lb) and \none (1) fully collapsible stroller or carry-cot as a carry-on item, as long as cabin space is available and you are not bringing a child seat. If no space is available in the cabin,\n the stroller/carry-cot must be transported as checked baggage in the hold.  ");
        FAQ3QC1.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QC1, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 80, 1060, 260));

        FAQ3QDF1.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 16)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QDF1.setText("<html>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp <b>Handbag:</b> 55 x 38 x 20cm (22 x 15 x 8 inches)");
        FAQ3QDF1.setOpaque(true);
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QDF1, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 350, 1060, 50));

        FAQ3QB2.setHorizontalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.CENTER);
        FAQ3QB2.setIcon(new javax.swing.ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/Images/Bullet.png"))); // NOI18N
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QB2, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(30, 450, 40, 30));

        FAQ3QH2.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 24)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QH2.setText("<html><b>Are there additional baggage allowances for passengers with disabilities?\n");
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QH2, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 450, -1, 30));

        FAQ3QC2.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 16)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QC2.setText("<html>Passengers with special requirements are entitled to certain additional baggage allowances, free of charge but subject to the following limitations:\n<ul>\n<li>Passengers with sleep disorders are permitted to carry one sleep apnea device, either CPAP (Continuous Positive Airway Pressure) or PAP (Positive Airway Pressure) as checked baggage subject to IATA Dangerous\nGoods Regulations. For information on the use of these devices in flight, please see our information on health and special needs.<br><br>\n<li>Passengers who are dependent on a wheelchair may travel with a fully collapsible wheelchair stored in the aircraft hold. Passengers who are dependent on braces or crutches may also travel with these items stored\nin the aircraft hold.<br><br>\n<li>Passengers who are dependent on a portable kidney dialysis machine are entitled to travel with one machine and ancillary equipment loaded in the aircraft hold.<br><br>\n<li>Assistance dogs of vision and hearing-impaired passengers may be loaded in the hold in kennels and will not be permitted in the cabin.<br><br>\n</ul></html>");
        FAQ3QC2.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QC2, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 500, 1060, 330));

        FAQ3QH3.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 24)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QH3.setText("<html><b>Can I carry my TV as checked baggage?\n\n");
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QH3, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 870, -1, 30));

        FAQ3QB3.setHorizontalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.CENTER);
        FAQ3QB3.setIcon(new javax.swing.ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/Images/Bullet.png"))); // NOI18N
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QB3, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(30, 870, 40, 30));

        FAQ3QC3.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 16)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QC3.setText("<html>There is no special free baggage allowance for the carriage of musical instruments. Musical instruments can be carried on Alpha Airlines flights in three different ways:\n<br><ul><li>as normal checked baggage, subject to the usual limitations<br><br>\n<li>as normal cabin baggage, subject to the usual limitations<br><br>\n<li>as cabin baggage on an unoccupied seat in the passenger cabin if the instrument is within the usual size and weight limits for carry-on items, or on a paid-for seat in the passenger cabin if the instrument exceeds those limits.<br><br>\n</ul>\nPlease note that certain specific conditions and limitations on the options outlined above apply to particular musical instruments. If your itinerary includes flights operated by other airlines, different baggage rules may apply for these flights.");
        FAQ3QC3.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QC3, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 1220, 1060, 280));

        FAQ3QH4.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 24)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QH4.setText("<html><b>Are there special baggage allowances for musical instruments?\n\n");
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QH4, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 1170, -1, 30));

        FAQ3QB4.setHorizontalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.CENTER);
        FAQ3QB4.setIcon(new javax.swing.ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/Images/Bullet.png"))); // NOI18N
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QB4, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(30, 1170, 40, 30));

        FAQ3QC4.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Microsoft JhengHei UI", 0, 16)); // NOI18N
        FAQ3QC4.setText("<html>Customers are allowed to carry TVs as checked baggage. However, as this is a fragile electronic device we require the TV to have appropriate packaging in order to withstand the normal rigours of air travel.\n<br><br>Effective from 1 May 2019, when checking in your TV you will be charged a handling fee of 75 USD, and will also need to sign a limited release. \nYou can check in TVs up to 300cm (118 inches) with a total weight not exceeding 32kg (70lb).\n<br><br>\nThe TV may be subject to overweight or oversized baggage fees depending on your baggage allowance. Please note that acceptance of TVs as checked baggage will depend on the airport you are departing from or arriving to. We\nrecommend contacting the airport directly before travel.");
        FAQ3QC4.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        FAQ3Panel.add(FAQ3QC4, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(70, 920, 1060, 200));

